result.execSummary:
Tanner Jess Rix was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Tanner Jess Rix was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: of the plea hearing held before the Honorable Eric J. Lundell on 03-18-2015, filed by RMR V. Deiss. gme
signed by Defendant and EJL this date. eif

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Michael E. Nieskes, DF ATTY: Brian Thomas Smestad,  ATTY: Alex Andrea DF: Tanner Jess Rix appeared from jail.  Court called at 1:07 p.m.  Includes 14CF400 (Plea/Sentencing) & 15CF122 (Initial).  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Attorney Andrea recites the agreement.  Attorney Nieskes advises the court the DE has made a statement to Wabasha County admitting to the homicide taking place in Minnesota.  Attorneys are asking the court to set out sentencing for 6 months to allow for Minnesota to prosecute the DE with regards to the homicide.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads No Contest to Ct 2 (with the repeater stricken) in 14CF400.  Attorney's stipulate to the facts.  Court finds factual basis and Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.   Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct  2 (with the repeater stricken) in 14CF400. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 1 held open and Ct. 3 & Ct. 4 without prejudice in 14CF400.  Court reserves on a PSI at this time.  Court modifies Bail Bond to a $100,000 signature bond.  

In 15CF122 (Initial) DE waives his right to extradition back to Minnesota.  Court questions the DE.  Crt finds the DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights to challenge extradition.  DE signs extradition documents.  DE to be held without bond. Court adjourned at 1:33 p.m. lw
